main event: A civilian astronomer observed a bright, fast-moving object in the sky near Alice, Texas on September 7, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed to be round in shape, with a light similar to the planet Venus.
The object moved at a fast rate of speed in a smooth, straight trajectory from south to north.
The observer used 7x binoculars to view the object.
The object was initially mistaken for the Echo II satellite, but the observer concluded it was an unidentified flying object.
sighted object: A round, bright object in the sky
photographs: No photographs were included in the report.
